= Schleicher and the Industrialists

The German industrialists and big business leaders have maintained a friendly stance toward Schleicher, appreciating his prioritization of their interests over those of the agrarians and his efforts to stabilize the economy. However, concerns linger over his growing state intervention and the risk that his public works campaign could trigger runaway inflation.

To address this, Schleicher has summoned a secret meeting with his allies and Germany’s leading industrialists. He will offer sweeping concessions: a guarantee of capitalism’s preservation and their continued dominance over labor within a corporatist framework. In return, they are expected to pool their resources for unrestricted use by the <span style="color: #BFC8CC;">**DNEF**</span>.

