Schleicher continues to walk a tightrope between appeasing organized labor and retaining the favor of Germany’s industrial elite. Nonetheless, the <span style="color: #BFC8CC;">**DNEF**</span> secures over five million marks in funding from a consortium of German businesses—chiefly those tied to rearmament, who see Schleicher’s survival as essential to their own profits.